util.validation

Class TwoTokenParser<X,Y>

  • java.lang.Object
    • util.validation.TwoTokenParser<X,Y>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ObjectParser<Pair<X,Y>>

    public class TwoTokenParser<X,Y>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ObjectParser<Pair<X,Y>>
    Combines two parsers into one that applies the fist parser to the first token and the second parser to the second token to produce a parsed pair.

      • parseNonNull

        public Either<java.lang.String,Pair<X,Y>> parseNonNull(java.util.stream.Stream<java.lang.String> tokens)
        Description copied from interface: ObjectParser
        Same as ObjectParser.parse(Stream) but doesn't check if the argument is null. This is the only method you need to implement as you can rely on the default implementation of ObjectParser.parse(Stream) to do the check.
